                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15952.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-28T20:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 28, 1915—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s August 28, 1 p.m. Foreign Office says strict orders have been given
                    to military commander of zone and other generals to prevent any disorder on
                    Mexican side. Asks same instructions on American side. Arredondo has been
                    instructed to make representation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
